The paper proposes a privacy-preserving algorithm for the Expectation Maximization (EM) algorithm, which is a widely used iterative algorithm in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also discusses privacy concerns and proposes a solution, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The algorithm leverages the exponential family of models, which is a statistical concept, indicating that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of differential privacy, which is a privacy concept, indicating that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper proposes a general approach that can be extended to other iterative machine learning algorithms, indicating that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
